    <title>Burch index, summands of syzygies and linearity in resolutions</title>
    <summary>  The Burch index is a new invariant of a local ring $R$ whose positivity
implies a kind of linearity in resolutions of $R$-modules. For example, if $R$
has depth zero and Burch index at least $2$, then any non-free 7th $R$-syzygy
contains the residue field as a direct summand. We also compute the Burch index
in various cases of interest.
</summary>
